  <description type="morphology">Stems erect, from stolons turning away from substrate. Stem leaves 1.2–2 × 0.2–0.9 mm; apex gradually, broadly acuminate, often appearing abruptly so because of subapical recurved margins; costa often obscured by plicae, especially distally; alar cells in 7–15 rows, extending along margins by 25–50 cells, collenchymatous; medial laminal cells 42–71 × 4 µm. Sporophytes unknown.</description>
